 writes and git commits)\\n\\n- **`Name()`** → `\\\"factoryai-droid\\\"`\\n\\n- **`IsAvailable()`** — `exec.LookPath(\\\"droid\\\")` + check `FACTORY_API_KEY` is set (droid requires API key auth, unlike Claude which uses OAuth)\\n\\n- **`RunPromptWithTools()`** — build and execute:\\n  ```\\n  droid exec --cwd <workDir> --auto medium -o text [--enabled-tools <tools>] [-m <model>] \\\"<prompt>\\\"\\n  ```\\n\\nRegister in `NewAgentRunner()` switch: `case AgentNameFactoryAIDroid:` → `NewFactoryAIDroidRunner(config)`\\n\\n### 2. Update `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/testenv.go`\\n\\nIn `NewFeatureBranchEnv()` — the `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY` env vars are set in `GitCommitWithShadowHooks`. Check that droid hooks get appropriate env. The existing `RunEntireEnable` already passes `--agent defaultAgent` so it should work for droid out of the box.\\n\\nNo changes expected here — just verify.\\n\\n### 3. Adjust agent-specific test skips (if any)\\n\\nReview existing scenarios for Claude-specific assumptions. `scenario_subagent_test.go` already skips for non-Claude agents. The JSONL validation in `ValidateCheckpoint` already has `isClaudeCode` conditional. Droid uses JSONL too, so validation should pass.\\n\\nNo changes expected — just verify.\\n\\n## Files Modified\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/agent_runner.go` — add `FactoryAIDroidRunner` (~80 lines)\\n\\n## Run E2E Tests\\n\\n```bash\\n# Requires droid CLI installed and FACTORY_API_KEY set\\nE2E_AGENT=factoryai-droid go test -tags=e2e -run TestE2E_BasicWorkflow ./cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/...\\n\\n# With specific model\\nE2E_AGENT=factoryai-droid E2E_DROID_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929 go test -tags=e2e ./cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/...\\n```\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint` — passes\\n2. `mise run test:ci` — unit + integration tests still pass\\n3. Manual: `E2E_AGENT=factoryai-droid go test -tags=e2e -run TestE2E_BasicWorkflow -v ./cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/...` — basic workflow completes\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":